---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout>
    <section class="pt-24 pb-16 px-6 bg-white min-h-screen">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-800 mb-6 leading-tight">
                Acueductos de Cantalloc
            </h1>
            <img src="/cantalloc.webp" alt="Acueductos de Cantalloc" class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-lg mb-8" />

            <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 text-lg">
                <p>
                    Includes a visit to three archaeological sites:
                </p>

                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800">
                            <i class="fas fa-water mr-2 text-blue-600"></i> 
                            Cantalloc Aqueducts:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            Explore a one-of-a-kind underground hydraulic system, built by the ancient Nazca people to harness water in the middle of the desert. Still in operation, these spiral aqueducts demonstrate this culture's advanced engineering and sustainability expertise.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                <div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800">
                    <i class="fas fa-landmark mr-2 text-yellow-600"></i> 
                    Paredones Archaeological Complex:
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Visit the ruins of an ancient Inca administrative center built from adobe. This site offers a unique insight into the encounter between the Inca and Nasca cultures, with structures such as colcas (storage chambers), platforms, and ceremonial paths.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800">
                    <i class="fas fa-eye mr-2 text-pink-600"></i> 
                    Needle and Loom Geoglyphs
                </h2>
                <p>
                    End the tour by admiring these impressive geoglyphs traced across the pampas from a viewpoint. They depict textile implements and clearly reflect the importance of textile art in the Nasca worldview.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-base pt-4">
            <li>
                <strong>
                    Approximate duration:    
                </strong> 
                2 a 2.5 hours
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>
                    Departure from:
                </strong> 
                City of Nasca
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>
                    Includes:
                </strong> 
                Tourist transportation, Specialized local guide, Photo and rest stops.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="pt-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">
                <i class="fas fa-sun mr-2 text-orange-400"></i> 
                Recommendations:
            </h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-base">
                <li>
                    Bring sunscreen, a hat, and water.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Comfortable footwear
                </li>
                <li>
                    Camera
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mt-10">
            <a href="/#tours" class="text-blue-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg border border-blue-600 text-base font-medium hover:bg-blue-50 transition">
                <i class="fas fa-arrow-left mr-2"></i> Back to Itineraries
            </a>
            <a href="https://wa.link/0voy2n" class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg text-base font-medium hover:bg-blue-700 transition" target="_blank">
                <i class="fa-brands fa-whatsapp"></i>
                Request Reservation
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>